editary surname."],"variants":[{"name":"McQueen","meanings":["Scottish and Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Shuibhne</b> ‘son of <i>Suibhne</i>’ a byname meaning ‘pleasant’. Compare   McSweeney  .","Scottish and Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Shuain</b>, a Gaelic patronymic based on Old Norse <i>sveinn</i> ‘boy, servant’, which was also used as a personal name (see   Swain  ). This is given as the origin of the McQueen or McSwan family of Skye, although the spellings are hard to distinguish. Compare   Whan  .","Americanized form of French   Moquin  ."]}]},{"name":"Nest","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Latinized version of <i>Nest</i>, a Welsh pet form of <b>Agnes</b> ; the name of the grandmother of the 12th-century chronicler Giraldus Cambrensis (‘Gerald the Welshman’)."],"variants":[]},{"name":"ferch","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["German: variant of   Ferg  . Compare   Verch  .","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förtsch</b> (see   Foertsch  ).","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förch</b> (see   Foerch  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Ferg","meanings":["1  ‘Sharp blade’.","2  ‘Wind’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Queen Nest ferch Cadell was born in 0770, in Montgomery, Montgomeryshire, Wales, her father, Cadell ap Brochfael King of Powys, was 9 and her mother, Nest verch Cadell, was 28. She had at least 1 son with Merfyn \"Frych the Freckled\" ap Gwriad. She died in 0825, in Anglesey, Wales, United Kingdom, at the age of 55."},"et":{"770–825":"0770–0825","0770–0825":"0770–0825","0778–0855":"0778–0855","0780–0853":"0780–0853","0795–0844":"0795–0844","0820–0878":"0820–0878","0762–0808":"0762–0808","0742–0811":"0742–0811","0808":"0808","0780":"0780","770":"0770","0820":"0820","0853":"0853","0742":"0742","about 0820":"umbes 0820","0762":"0762","0795":"0795","0770":"0770